- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the development of a new programming language and its evaluation using various metrics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper specifically focuses on Visual Programming Languages (VPLs) and their evaluation. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the paper discusses the usability and user-friendliness of the VPLs. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper discusses the impact of VPLs on learning computer programming and their potential use in business applications. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the development of an information system using the new programming language.
